spec: mp3181
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__, __floordiv__, __mod__ dict-presence for multiprocessing types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, multiprocessing.pool.Pool, multiprocessing.pool.AsyncResult, multiprocessing.pool.MapResult, multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager, multiprocessing.managers.BaseListProxy, multiprocessing.managers._BaseDictProxy, multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__truediv__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __truediv__. True division (/) is not defined for any multiprocessing type. Notably, this includes the 3 manager proxy classes: BaseListProxy (proxies list), _BaseDictProxy (proxies dict), and _BaseSetProxy (proxies set). Python's built-in list, dict, and set do not define __truediv__ — consequently, neither do their proxies. list / n, dict / n, and set / n are all invalid Python expressions."
    - "Key finding (__floordiv__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __floordiv__. Floor division (//) is not defined for any multiprocessing type. Again, all 3 proxy classes return false: the underlying list, dict, and set types do not define __floordiv__. list // n, dict // n, set // n are all invalid. multiprocessing.Process, Pool, AsyncResult, MapResult, SyncManager: process and pool management objects with no floor division semantics."
    - "Key finding (__mod__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __mod__. Modulo (%) is not defined for any multiprocessing type, including all 3 proxy classes. Python's list, dict, and set do not define __mod__ — lists use indexing and slicing, dicts use key lookup, sets use set-algebraic operators. The proxies faithfully reflect the absence of __mod__ on their underlying types."
    - "Contrast with wave 658 (mp3166): BaseListProxy had __add__=true and __mul__=true; _BaseSetProxy had __sub__=true. Those were the proxy classes faithfully mirroring list's + and * and set's -. In this wave, none of list, dict, or set define __truediv__, __floordiv__, or __mod__, so all proxies return false."
    - "Proxy arithmetic profile update after wave 659:"
    - "  BaseListProxy  (proxies list): __add__=true, __sub__=false, __mul__=true, __truediv__=false, __floordiv__=false, __mod__=false"
    - "  _BaseDictProxy (proxies dict): all arithmetic false (dict has no +/-/*// or % in its own __dict__)"
    - "  _BaseSetProxy  (proxies set):  __sub__=true (set difference); all others false"
    - "Cross-wave summary for all mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 652 (mp3076): __get__/__set__/__delete__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 653 (mp3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 654 (mp3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ — _BaseSetProxy true; others false."
    - "  Wave 655 (mp3121): __ge__ — _BaseSetProxy true; __repr__ — Pool true; __str__ all false."
    - "  Wave 656 (mp3136): __call__ all false; __len__ — 3 proxies true; __getitem__ — list+dict true."
    - "  Wave 657 (mp3151): __setitem__/__delitem__ — list+dict proxies true; __contains__ — all 3 proxies true."
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy true; __sub__ — _BaseSetProxy true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __truediv__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__truediv__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __truediv__.
# multiprocessing.Process: process lifecycle object; no division protocol.
# multiprocessing.pool.Pool: worker pool; pool / n is not defined.
# multiprocessing.pool.AsyncResult/MapResult: result containers; no division.
# multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager: manager for shared-state objects; no /.
# multiprocessing.managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list; list.__truediv__ is
#   not defined — list / n is a TypeError. The proxy mirrors this absence.
# multiprocessing.managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict; dict.__truediv__ is
#   not defined — dict / n is a TypeError. The proxy mirrors this absence.
# multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set; set.__truediv__ is
#   not defined — set / n is a TypeError. The proxy mirrors this absence.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

